{"TIRADE":[{"def":"A declamatory strain or flight of censure or abuse; a rambling invective; an oration or harangue abounding in censorious and bitter language.","pos":""}],"TIRAILLEUR":[{"def":"Formerly, a member of an independent body of marksmen in the French army.","pos":""}],"TIRE":[{"def":"A tier, row, or rank.","pos":""}],"TIRE-WOMAN":[{"def":"A dresser in a theater.","pos":""}],"TIRED":[{"def":"Weary; fatigued; exhausted.","pos":""}],"TIREDNESS":[{"def":"The state of being tired, or weary.","pos":""}],"TIRELING":[{"def":"Tired; fatigued.","pos":""}],"TIRESOME":[{"def":"Fitted or tending to tire; exhausted; wearisome; fatiguing; tedious; as, a tiresome journey; a tiresome discourse.","pos":""}],"TIRING-ROOM":[{"def":"The room or place where players dress for the stage.","pos":""}],"TIRL":[{"def":"To quiver; to vibrate; to veer about.","pos":""},{"def":"To make a ratting or clattering sound by twirling or shaking; as, to tirl at the pin, or latch, of a door.","pos":""}],"TIRMA":[{"def":"The oyster catcher.","pos":""}],"TIRONIAN":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to Tiro, or a system of shorthand said to have been introduced by him into ancient Rome.","pos":""}],"TIRRALIRRA":[{"def":"A verbal imitation of a musical sound, as of the note of a lark or a horn.","pos":""}],"TIRRIT":[{"def":"A word from the vocabulary of Mrs.","pos":""}],"TIRWIT":[{"def":"A common contraction of it is.","pos":""}]}